Python File Sorter
==================

A simple script that automatically organizes files in a directory into subfolders based on their file extensions.

Features:
---------
- Sorts files by type (e.g., images, documents, videos, etc.)
- Automatically creates folders for each type
- Easily customizable extension mappings

How to Use:
-----------
1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/JonSalves/Python-File-sorter.git

2. Run the script:
   python file_sorter.py

3. The files in the target folder will be sorted into subdirectories.

Requirements:
-------------
- Python 3.x
- OS module (standard library)

Notes:
------
- Update the `extension_mapping` dictionary to add or modify categories.
